body:
@FrozenGene 
I delayed on the align_corners (NN) with your caution of OpenCL check and GPU testing.
I would probably conclude this PR to unify the API up to frontend without align_corners(NN) and then work on the align_corners(NN) compute for GPU & OpenCL.

@masahi , @FrozenGene & @tqchen 
Please have a look at this unification patches and comment.
I would add some test cases on this unified version based on the comments.

@kaishijeng 
Did you make corresponding changes to from_tensorflow utility ?

Mobilenet input node name is "input", hence

shape_dict = {'input': x.shape}
dtype_dict = {'input': x.dtype}

Ref. Below patch with changes to the utility for mobilenet. You just need to change tf model, image paths.
https://github.com/srkreddy1238/tvm/commit/edd72d6904b69ae266cf5067fddbb6487dc4d291.patch

@srkreddy1238 

Tensorflow takes 0.729sec which is longer than tvm/nnvm, 0.45sec

Thanks,

@srkreddy1238 

I noticed from_tensorflow.py uses just one CPU core even RK3399 have 6 cores. Is there a way to enable from_tensorflow.py to use all CPU cores?

Thanks,

@srkreddy1238 

Do you have a plan to support mobilenet-ssd?

Thanks,

@kaishijeng 

SSD operator support at TVM/NNVM is under review in some other PR https://github.com/dmlc/tvm/pull/1214

Once it's merged I would definitely consider to add front end support.

@yzhliu @Laurawly @zhreshold please provide further comments or approval.

Let us aim to bring this in as it is an important change.

@kevinthesun please list the TODOs to enable a gluon-cv model and we can work towards that in a separate PR
